item.title: HOW DO I DELETE A OBJECT whats already there
item.dc:creator: @xxlukexx xxlukexx
item.description:
@xxlukexx wrote:

[quote=“Runeter, post:7, topic:269096”]I took the above tutorial and added code tags and such, so it will be easier to understand and such.

[center]--------------------------------------------[/center]

deletethatwill void right here

Purpose: To delete Doors and other object that can’t be deleted by the deletethatobject.

Difficulty: 1/10

Files modified: Client.java

Ok, when i had my own server, this one already had the deletethatwall void… Now i’m coding on Stillscape (deltabased) and it didn’t have the deletethatwall void… I tried the C & P of Someone named Owned Reaper or something like that but it’s missing something to work… I can’t believe i find the thing it missed myself LOL Tongue

FIRST TUT, DON’T FLAME PLEASE! MAKE SUGGESTIONS!

Search for

public void deletethatobject(int objectX, int objectY) { ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 10); }

Then, under the last }, add the following:

public void deletethatwall(int objectX, int objectY) { ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 0); } Ok now look for: Code: public void makeGlobalObject And just ABOVE it add: Code: public void Deletewalls() { deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY); deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY); }

The XXXX and the YYYY is the coordinates of the door or whatever you want to delete (That you can’t delete with deletethatobject)

Ok, now, the little thing i figured out myself, i was so pround (LOL:P)!

Search for:

case 121

You should see something like:

replaceDoors(); // if(heightLevel == 1) // ReplaceObject(2591, 3107, 375, -3, 11); // we could use this to make the char appear for other players only // until // this guys loading is done. Also wait with regular player updates // until we receive this command. // println_debug("Loading finished."); Deleteobjects(); writePlayers(); NewObjects(); hasntLoggedin = true; //server.checkPlayerCapes.processAll(this); if(!isInWilderness(absX, absY, 1)){ setInterfaceWalkable(-1); hasWildySign = false; } break;

Ok, under “Deleteobjects();” add this:

Deletewalls();

Here you go! 100% promising you it works

COMMENTS PLEASE IF IT HELPED! (Or just for telling me “Great Guid Duuude!” Tongue[/quote]

thats just bascially spamming mate, there is no need for that when he posted a tut.

item.description:
@Runeter wrote:

I took the above tutorial and added code tags and such, so it will be easier to understand and such. And i’m goann test this tutorial on Delta, and I’ll post later if it works.

[center]--------------------------------------------[/center]

deletethatwill void right here

Purpose: To delete Doors and other object that can’t be deleted by the deletethatobject.

Difficulty: 1/10

Files modified: Client.java

Ok, when i had my own server, this one already had the deletethatwall void… Now i’m coding on Stillscape (deltabased) and it didn’t have the deletethatwall void… I tried the C & P of Someone named Owned Reaper or something like that but it’s missing something to work… I can’t believe i find the thing it missed myself LOL Tongue

FIRST TUT, DON’T FLAME PLEASE! MAKE SUGGESTIONS!

Search for

public void deletethatobject(int objectX, int objectY) { ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 10); }

Then, under the last }, add the following:

public void deletethatwall(int objectX, int objectY) { ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 0); }

Ok, now look for.

public void makeGlobalObject

And just ABOVE it add:

public void Deletewalls() { deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY); deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY); }

The XXXX and the YYYY is the coordinates of the door or whatever you want to delete (That you can’t delete with deletethatobject)

Ok, now, the little thing i figured out myself, i was so pround (LOL:P)!

Search for:

case 121

You should see something like:

replaceDoors(); // if(heightLevel == 1) // ReplaceObject(2591, 3107, 375, -3, 11); // we could use this to make the char appear for other players only // until // this guys loading is done. Also wait with regular player updates // until we receive this command. // println_debug("Loading finished."); Deleteobjects(); writePlayers(); NewObjects(); hasntLoggedin = true; //server.checkPlayerCapes.processAll(this); if(!isInWilderness(absX, absY, 1)){ setInterfaceWalkable(-1); hasWildySign = false; } break;

Ok, under “Deleteobjects();” add this:

Deletewalls();

Here you go! 100% promising you it works

COMMENTS PLEASE IF IT HELPED! (Or just for telling me “Great Guid Duuude!” Tongue

item.description:
@xxlukexx wrote:

[quote=“myspaceman123, post:4, topic:269096”]deletethatwill void right here

Purpose: To delete Doors and other object that can’t be deleted by the deletethatobject.

Difficulty: 1/10

Files modified: Client.java

Ok, when i had my own server, this one already had the deletethatwall void… Now i’m coding on Stillscape (deltabased) and it didn’t have the deletethatwall void… I tried the C & P of Someone named Owned Reaper or something like that but it’s missing something to work… I can’t believe i find the thing it missed myself LOL

FIRST TUT, DON’T FLAME PLEASE! MAKE SUGGESTIONS!

Search for
Code:
public void deletethatobject(int objectX, int objectY) {
ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 10);
}
Then, under the last }, add the following:
Code:
public void deletethatwall(int objectX, int objectY) {
ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 0);
}
Ok now look for:
Code:
public void makeGlobalObject
And just ABOVE it add:
Code:
public void Deletewalls() {
deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY);
deletethatwall(XXXX, YYYY);
}
The XXXX and the YYYY is the coordinates of the door or whatever you want to delete (That you can’t delete with deletethatobject)

Ok, now, the little thing i figured out myself, i was so pround (LOL:P)!

Search for:
Code:
case 121
You should see something like:
Code:
replaceDoors();
// if(heightLevel == 1)
// ReplaceObject(2591, 3107, 375, -3, 11);
// we could use this to make the char appear for other players only
// until
// this guys loading is done. Also wait with regular player updates
// until we receive this command.
// println_debug(“Loading finished.”);
Deleteobjects();
writePlayers();
NewObjects();
hasntLoggedin = true;
//server.checkPlayerCapes.processAll(this);
if(!isInWilderness(absX, absY, 1)){
setInterfaceWalkable(-1);
hasWildySign = false;
}
break;
Ok, under “Deleteobjects();” add this:
Code:
Deletewalls();
Here you go! 100% promising you it works
